channel.title: [FIRST] Trivium Symbol [/FIRST]
channel.description:
This is my first model. So I'd appreciate constructive criticism. It's the trivium symbol. The original is here... [IMG]http://media.musictoday.com/store/bands/1022/product_medium/BGAMTV07.JPG[/img]
Mine is here.. [IMG]http://i183.photobucket.com/albums/x34/luke_livez/triviummq-1.jpg[/img] Rendering: [IMG]http://i183.photobucket.com/albums/x34/luke_livez/triviummq1.jpg[/img] I was REALLY bored. And modelling is a lot of fun. Gtfo I know it's not 3D. It's not supposed to be. What do you guys think?

item.dc:creator: @P_I_M_P_3_D_Tut `Lewk_
item.description:
@P_I_M_P_3_D_Tut wrote:

CoonHunter:

I’ll be honest, its nice for a outline. Yet, for a model it sucks. (Could have been further into zoom and made a more detailed version). Also, yea, use ACF’s advice on that. For a good idea just use google images for a 2d sword. (when you get decient u can convert that 2d into a 3d).

Thanks for the feedback.

[quote=“Assassins Creed Fan, post:4, topic:285919”]Quite basic isn’t it?
I’d suggest you to read CJ’s tut
Make a basic/normal sword , and experiment with the program itself.
Other then that, it isn’t a skillcape nor a recolor .
Good job on that :P[/quote]
Thanks.
